.TH "CARETPOSITION.GETCLIENTRECT" "3JS" "September 15, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
CaretPosition.getClientRect \- CaretPosition: getClientRect() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]getClientRect()\f[R] method of the \f[CR]CaretPosition\f[R]
interface returns the client rectangle for the caret range.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getClientRect()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
A \f[CR]DOMRect\f[R] object.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Get the caret\(cqs screen position
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]input\f[R] aria\-label=\(dqtext field\(dq value=\(dqClick inside this input field\(dq />
.EE
.IP
.EX
document.querySelector(\(dqinput\(dq).addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] x = event.clientX;
  \f[B]const\f[R] y = event.clientY;

  \f[B]const\f[R] caret = document.caretPositionFromPoint?.(x, y);
  \f[B]if\f[R] (!caret) {
    log(\(dqNot supported\(dq);
    \f[B]return\f[R];
  }

  \f[B]const\f[R] rect = caret.getClientRect();

  log(\(gaCaret bounding rect: ${JSON.stringify(rect)}\(ga);
  log(\(gaCaret is at (${rect.x.toFixed(2)}, ${rect.y.toFixed(2)})\(ga);
});
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]DOMRect\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]Document.caretPositionFromPoint()\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]Element.getBoundingClientRect()\f[R]
